        <p><strong>Frederick Phillips Brooks, Jr.</strong> (born 19 April 1931) is a computer architect, software engineer, and computer scientist, best known for managing the development of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IBM', 'C'); ?>'s System/360 family of computers and the OS/360 software support package, then later writing candidly about the process in his seminal book <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('The Mythical Man-Month', 'B'); ?>.</p>
        <p>Brooks has received many awards, including the National Medal of Technology in 1985 and the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Turing Award', 'IT'); ?> in 1999.</p>
